<br>
How they do this without screwing up current encounters I have no idea, but it should have been obvious that warriors should tank better from the beginning. Somehow that fact was missed by the development team at the time, and as sucky as it is, is not something simple to repair.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If I understand you correctly you basically concede in the above that Warriors don't have noticeably better mitigation, without using a discipline.  And that to make that happen would impact encounters pretty much game wide.  Going back and fixing it probably isn't an option, would you agree?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As for those that believe warriors should get improved agro, I simply cannot agree. No class should get the best of both worlds. Make holding a MOBs attention equal some amount of work is fine and in my mind welcome, but the reward for that needs to be a superior ability to deal with that attention. I am in the group of people that could care less if knights can grab agro at will, just need to make sure warriors bring something to the table to make them a viable choice in tanks.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yet here, if I understand you, you're saying that giving Warriors improved aggro would be the best of both worlds.  You already pointed out that without a discipline a Warrior's mitigation isn't noticeably better than a Knights.  Yet a Knight's aggro control is noticeably better than a Warrior's.  How would narrowing the gap between Knight and Warrior aggro control be the best of both worlds when the mitigation difference, as you've already indicated and I agree, isn't noticeably different between the two?<br>
<br>
I would argue that currently the Knights have the best of both worlds.  They have mitigation which is not noticeably worse than a Warrior's and aggro control which puts a Warrior to shame.  If this would be broken on a Warrior, it is as equally broken on a Knight.  Either Warrior mitigation needs a boost, unlikely to happen, Warrior aggro control needs a boost, which is possible, or Knight mitigation needs to be dropped, unlikely to happen, or Knight aggro control needs to drop, also unlikely to happen.  There really is only one course of action which, to me, appears viable.<br>
 <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
