<br>
How they do that I am not really sure. I have no way of testing any ideas I can think of, nor the time to sit and brainstorm an idea =p<br>
<br>
I still do not see how adding great agro to warriors is a fix. Knights will still be the better XP group choice. Warriors need to bring superior tanking skills to the table, or they will lose to knights, regardless of how much agro they can produce, because if tanking is almost equal, agro is almost equal.. the knight still brings a plethora of additional abilities.<br>
<br>
What I was really trying to say is that this whole issue is not as simple as adding 10% (some arbitrary number I just made up) mitigation to warriors. There will be repercusions throughtout the game by making that change, and I think many warriors do not really appreciate the impact it may have. Sometimes we get caught up in class balance, without even thinking about game balance.<br>
<br>
Point is, in my opinion the best route is to revamp warriors defensive abilities, while trying not to instantly trivialize numerous encounters. It wont be easy, and it wont be fast, but they get paid to do it not me.<br>
<br>
