Almost the whole thread is a bunch of bazaar equipped &lt;65 warriors wondering why they arent as desireable in a group as a 65 Knight with 100+ AAXP and NO DROP PoP gear.<br>
<br>
Most of the warriors are claiming what they have &quot;seen&quot; a knight do and haven't posted a single parse or set of numbers to prove their point...  not one of them has addressed the fact that I have &quot;seen&quot; a warrior hold aggro with 200+ AAXP damage dealing classes in the group...<br>
<br>
Warriors DO make better tanks...  they mitigate better through avoidance (skill caps) as well as 1000hp... thats 10% more HP for the math-impaired.  The avoidance is NOT that much better without disc in the long run, that much is true.<br>
<br>
When the avoid benefits start showing themselves is when you have less than 20% health left and that mob misses at the right time...  dying = downtime... ESPECIALLY for a knight.<br>
<br>
Warriors real issue here is aggro... and most importantly aggro when they aren't wielding EB items...  warrior mitigation is actually quite good.<br>
<br>
<br>
Warriors who say they are only there to &quot;take&quot; damage are full of it...  you are there to kill things and gain XP.  Faster dead things = better...  faster ded things with no cost to the party = wonderful.  Warriors with a Blade of War are monstrously wonderful tanks AND damage dealers.<br>
<br>
That ONE drop closes the aggro gap quite nicely...<br>
<br>
It takes me 5-6 100+ Hp items over what the warrior has to TOUCH their HP...<br>
<br>
