Is aggro generation supposed to be hard or is it supposed to be easy?  If you're a Warrior, it's supposed to be hard.  If you're a Knight, it's supposed to be easy.  Why would it be different between the two?  The Warriors have defensive?  Naw, not much use in an experience group.  The Warriors have better mitigation?  Hardly universally true and extremely open to debate.  Warriors have more HP?  Usually true, but in PoP of much less value than previously.  The Warriors do more damage?  Only when compared to a Paladin, and otherwise pretty laughable compared to other classes that specialize in damage.<br>
<br>
All other things being as equal as they are, and I think everyone knows that they're much closer to being completely equal between the Knights and the Warriors than ever before, the difference in aggro generation is the one huge glaring difference.<br>
<br>
Whether you think Warrior aggro generation is too little or Knight aggro generation is too much, if you're a rational human being, you have to admit that the difference between the two is too dramatic given the much smaller differences between the them in other ways.<br>
<br>
